u Ishiba, according to Reuters, sent a letter to the US President asking him to approve the deal so as not to harm recent efforts to strengthen ties between the two countries.\\n\\nTags:", "score": 0.6836946, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.mining-technology.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger", "title": "US Steel, Nippon Steel merger gains nod of non-US regulators", "content": "United States Steel Corporation (US Steel) and Nippon Steel have secured all regulatory clearances from jurisdictions outside of the US for their proposed merger.\\n\\nThese approvals from the regulatory bodies mark a crucial step towards the completion of the deal, which is anticipated in the second half of 2024.\\n\\n### Go deeper with GlobalData\\n\\nReportsLogo\\n\\n#### Mining Industry Mergers and Acquisitions Deals by Top Themes in Q1 ...\\n\\nReportsLogo", "score": 0.6565047, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/nippon-steel-us-steel-send-letter-biden-merger-plans-2024-09-13", "title": "Nippon Steel, US Steel send letter to Biden on merger plans | Reuters", "content": "(CFIUS) told the companies in an Aug. 31 letter seen by Reuters the deal would create national security risks because it could hurt the supply of steel needed for critical transportation, infrastructure, construction and agriculture projects. A top Nippon Steel executive and U.S. Steel\'s CEO met with senior U.S. officials on Wednesday in an effort to salvage the deal, a person familiar with the matter said. The Japan Business Federation and a number of U.S. business groups, in a letter to", "score": 0.63615024, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://nwindianabusiness.com/community/business-news/u-s-steel-stockholders-approve-merger-with-nippon-steel/64321", "title": "U.S. Steel stockholders approve merger with Nippon Steel \\u2022 Northwest Indiana Business Magazine", "content": "\\u201cThis is an important milestone as we progress toward completing the transaction,\\u